1. The best title for the passage would be _____.  
(ANSWER:A)
a. Unlocking the Multiple Nature of Code Switching  
b. Languages and Different Experiences  
c. Persuasive Accent of Languages  
d. Multilingual People and Their Lifestyles   
  
  
2. We can understand that people tend to speak their mother language while they get angry 
because _____________.  
(ANSWER: D)
a. They do not know words about feelings in their second language  
b. Mother languages generally are not very suitable for quarrels  
c. The parents always speak Spanish when they get angry   
d. Emotions show themselves more easily and comfortably in mother language  
  
3. Why does Anabel, as a sales clerk, make more sales when she speaks with a southern accent?  
(ANSWER: C)
a. Southern accent has a variety of sales related to codes  
b. She can speak much faster in a southern accent  
c. People percept that southern accent is friendlier  
d. She can better practice sales techniques to persuade people in southern accent   
  
  
4. What is the definition of “code switching”?  
(ANSWER: B)
a. Forgetting the synonyms of words and explaining in a detailed way  
b. Changing between two or more languages within a single conversation  
c. Getting confused when talking and forgetting the correct codes of words  
d. Changing the meaning of words and confusing people in any speech  
  
  
5. “those” refers to ______.  
(ANSWER: B)
a. codes  
b. experiences  
c. reasons  
d. languages 